import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='ignore')
    yearly_disasters = data.groupby('Year').size().reset_index(name='Number of Disasters')
    
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Number of Disasters', data=yearly_disasters)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of natural disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='ignore')
    total_deaths_by_disaster = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Entity', y='Deaths', data=total_deaths_by_disaster)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('Which type of natural disaster has caused the most deaths?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('Year')['Deaths'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=data)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths caused by natural disasters per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='ignore')
    yearly_deaths = data.groupby('Year')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    max_year = yearly_deaths.loc[yearly_deaths['Deaths'].idxmax()]
    
    sns.barplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=yearly_deaths)
    plt.axvline(max_year['Year'], color='red', label=f"Max Deaths: {max_year['Deaths']:.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("Which year had the highest number of deaths caused by natural disasters?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
